<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-251-720  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 251 720.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  March 16 1990 n1386* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Adobe's Type Manager to go onto IBM Systems ApplicationArchitecture kit....andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Adobe Systems Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    ADBE.andO;Product:   Type Manager (Printer software) (marketing)IBM PS-2 (Microcomputer) (computer programs)Adobe Type Library (Computer font) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Page Description LanguagesFontsProduct DevelopmentBundled Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ADOBE'S TYPE MANAGER TO GO ONTO IBM SYSTEMSandM;APPLICATION ARCHITECTURE KIT...andM;As reported in CI No 1,378, Adobe Systems Inc's font technology, Adobe TypeManager, is now available for IBM personal computers and across all SystemsApplication Architecture-compliant systems.andP;  Adobe Type Manager, a softwareprogram that enables Macintosh users to display and print PostScript outlinefonts on both PostScript and non-PostScript output devices, will be availablefor users of Presentation Manager, Microsoft Windows and other MS-DOSapplications by the end of 1990.andP;  In addition, Adobe is upgrading the AdobeType Library to enable users to build bit-mapped fonts at any point size andprint them on both PostScript and Print Control Language printers, such asHewlett-Packard's LaserJet printer family.andP;  This upgrade will be available inthe summer of 1990.andP;  Adobe Systems Inc has also announced it has publishedthe Adobe Type 1 Font Format, a book containing the complete specificationsfor Adobe's Type 1 font format.andP;  The book, which costs $15, describes thesyntax, encoding of character outlines and the encryption and decryptionalgorithms.andO;</TEXT></DOC>